The Role 
 
The Software Developer role is a key role within the SMART (Site Monitoring, Analysis and Reporting Tool) team. The Software Developer role exists to architect, implement and support new software products for RES Support Services. 
 
The SMART team provides bespoke software solutions across the global wind, solar and energy storage Support Services business. This includes: 
 
 Retrieving and homogenizing data from a wide range of operational renewable energy power plants, in particular solar farms and wind farms 
 Analyzing operational data from renewable energy power plants, including data from Condition Monitoring Systems 
 Providing flexible reporting solutions for internal and external clients 
 Creating engineering analysis tools used by specialists to detect and prevent faults 
 Using machine learning and artificial intelligence to automate the application of specialist knowledge 
 
 The Software Developer has responsibilities including: 
 
 Working together with the Product Owner and subject matter experts to deliver new software products following the Scrum development methodology 
 Choosing the right technology, architecture and infrastructure for each product in consultation with other software developers and the Product Owner 
 Maintaining high operational performance; monitor and control exceptions and application availability and application performance 
 Assisting the Product Owner with user story definition and estimation 
 Demonstrating new features at wrap up meetings 
 Following and contributing to team working agreement 
 Contributing to the strategic technical direction of the product 
 Delivering work which is applicable to wind, solar and storage assets in all markets 
 Supporting continuous improvement of team tools and practices 
 
The Software Developer will work in a team which includes Software Developers, Product Owners, Software Support Specialists and Data Scientists. The roleâ€™s impact is to support growth of the Support Services business through quick integration of new renewable assets and excellent performance of existing analysis and reporting tools. 
 
We believe that small, empowered, self-motivated teams can do big things. We believe in ideas, in aspiring to be the best that we can be, work life balance and a blameless culture based on trusting our developers. 
 
